  "prompt": "Who survived being in the Bermuda Triangle?",
  "response": "Many people have survived incidents in the Bermuda Triangle, though the region is often associated with mysterious disappearances of ships and aircraft. One notable case is that of the USS Cyclops, a Navy cargo ship that vanished without a trace in 1918 while traveling through the area, but many other vessels and aircraft have safely passed through the region.\n\nSurvivor stories often come from smaller incidents, such as the experiences of individuals aboard private boats or small planes that encountered difficulties but ultimately made it back to safety. One famous survival story involves the pilot of a small plane who encountered a storm and was forced to ditch into the ocean. He survived by clinging to his aircraft or using life vests until he was rescued.\n\nWhile these stories may not be as widely publicized as tales of missing ships and planes, they highlight that not all experiences in the Bermuda Triangle end in tragedy.",
